<div id="nonValidatedInput" class="jigl-content-container">
  <h1>Non-validating Inputs</h1>
  <div class="jigl-content-description">
    Validation can be turned off on an input by adding the class <b>jigl-no-valid</b> to the root element.
    This can be very useful when creating a form where not everything is required and allow the user the
    option to supply the information or not. This JIGL option can be used with any other JIGL options, but
    it won't make a difference when using the minified input option or the disabled option.
  </div>
