  </code>
</div>

<div id="miniValidInput" class="jigl-content-container">
  <h1>Minified Validation</h1>
  <div class="jigl-content-description">
    Instead of using words to describe the state of the input, symbols can be used instead. This
    is especially useful when creating rows containing 4-6 inputs or inputs with long names to prevent
    the validation message from overwriting the field name. Adding the class <b>info-minify</b> to the 
    <b>jigl-info</b> element will kickstart the validation to change to the required symbols, but initially
    the "Required" text needs to be replaces with <i>&lt;i class="fa fa-exclamation"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;</i>.
    It requires a little more effort on the developers part to create one, but represents state in a very simple way.
    This JIGL option works with any other JIGL option, but won't make a difference when used with the disabled input
