<div id="disabledInput" class="jigl-content-container">
  <h1>Disabled Inputs</h1>
  <div class="jigl-content-description">
    Inputs can be disabled to allow a read-only field for an end user. This can be useful when showing off a profile or something
    along those lines where you would like the data to be displayed, but not altered. To use it add <b>jigl-disabled</b> to the 
    root tag of the input. This JIGL option works with any other JIGL option, but won't make a difference when used with the minified
    validation option or the no validation option.
  </div>
  <div class="jigl jigl-text jigl-disabled" tabindex="1">
    <div class="jigl-label">Input Name</div>
    <div class="jigl-container">
      <input class="jigl-field" type="text" name="inputName" value="Read-only Text" />
    </div>
  </div>
  <code class="jigl-content-code">
    <div>&lt;div class='jigl jigl-text jigl-disabled' tabindex='1'&gt;</div>
    <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;div class='jigl-label'&gt;Input Name&lt;/div&gt;</div>
